Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

User reported Kennametal India showing Sep 2022 as latest when reality
is Mar 2026 — 3.5 years stale, presented as current. Catastrophic for
an institutional tool. The root cause: Screener slug `/company/KENNAMET/`
returns an archived/wrong-canonical page (likely the company has an
alternate slug or a delisted-mirror). Bare-symbol returned 200 with
years-old data so our search-API fallback (which only fired on 4xx)
never triggered.

Three layers of defense:

A. STALENESS DETECTION (always runs)
   After full parse, compute monthsOld from the latest period header.
   If > 9 months old, set staleness.isStale = true and log a debug
   warning. The flag propagates through ScreenerInput → IndiaExtras
   so the UI knows to surface it.

B. AUTOMATIC RETRY (when initial parse looks stale)
   Quick post-fetch HTML scan finds the highest-year quarter header.
   If that year is ≥1 year behind current year, the page is suspect.
   Trigger Screener search API to find the canonical slug, re-fetch
   /company/{canonical}/consolidated/ with cache: 'no-store'. If
   that's fresher, replace the html. If still not, try the non-
   consolidated variant. If neither is fresher, keep the stale html
   so the staleness banner still warns the user.

C. UI BANNER (when staleness flag set)
   Red-bordered warning at the very top of the report:
   '⚠ STALE DATA WARNING — Latest reported period is Sep 2022 — that
   is 44 months old. The upstream source has not been updated…
   Treat numbers below as historical, not current.'

Effect for KENNAMET after deploy:
 - Auto-retry should find the canonical slug and pull current data
   (Mar 2026, Rev ₹403 Cr, EBITDA ₹77 Cr, PAT ₹51 Cr).
 - If retry fails for any reason, the red banner makes it impossible
   to mistake stale data for current.

Effect for any India ticker:
 - 9-month freshness gate triggers the banner.
 - Investor decisions can't be made silently against archived numbers.

